Next to DL's post.<br>
Wisdom and knowledge are not mutually exclusive.  However, I do not consider the knowledge of how many ridges appear on the edge of a quarter to be wisdom.  Oh, and I forgot something else that I've gained through my exposure to the coven is a greater knowledge of what most refer to as 'kitchen magick'.  For those who don't know, kitchen magick is using mixtures of herbs to help alleviate problems.  One of the mixtures that I'm good at is a potion to help overcome insomnia.  A few drops of lavender, clary sage and neroli oils are placed on a folded facecloth.  The facecloth is then placed upon the forehead of the person who is suffering from insomnia.  This mixture puts me to sleep in minutes, whereas without it I can often lie in bed for hours before falling asleep.<br>
<br>
ST.<br>
