Mixtures of herbs to alleviate problems….interesting.  Vague, and interesting.  The example cited is insomnia, so I tend to interpret this to mean we have a doctor here who brews his own medicines and calls it magic.  Most would call it pharmaceutical science, but hey, I have already been accused of being a definition nazi, so who am I to rule on this.  Of course, ‘problems’ is a word with many meanings.  If you can brew a potion that will get you out of debt or make it stop raining, those would be alleviating problems and more in keeping with ‘magic’ IMHO.  The question then becomes, do you believe that you can do those things and are just avoiding mentioning it to save credibility here?<br>
